#Entries
#Introduction
guide.prodigytech.entry.introduction.gettingstarted=Getting Started
guide.prodigytech.entry.introduction.gettingstarted.content=In order to progress in ProdigyTech, you'll need to make Ferramic in an Explosion Furnace. First collect a good supply of the required materials : Iron, Sand, Gunpowder and Clay.\nOnce you have enough of them, you can craft an Explosion Furnace and go to the next entry.

guide.prodigytech.entry.introduction.explosionfurnace.content1=The Explosion Furnace is the first machine to make. Using an explosive reaction, it can be used to turn Iron and Clay into Ferramic, a strong heat resistant material, as well as crush large amounts of Stone.
guide.prodigytech.entry.introduction.explosionfurnace.content2=Its GUI is split into 4 parts. On the left you have 2 vertical slots, the top one is the Explosive and the bottom one is the Reactant. On their right, you have 3 input slots, followed by the Reagent slot, and finally 3 output slots.
guide.prodigytech.entry.introduction.explosionfurnace.content3=To simply make Ferramic Ingots, put 5 Gunpowder in the Explosive slot, 4 Sand in the Reactant, 16 Iron Ingots in the input and 4 Clay in the Reagent slot (shift clicking or automation will sort them automatically), then stand back and give it a redstone pulse.
guide.prodigytech.entry.introduction.explosionfurnace.content4=You can double or triple the proportions as you want, and you can put too much Clay or Iron Ingots without consequences, but don't mess up the proportions on the explosive and reactant, otherwise items will be lost.

guide.prodigytech.entry.introduction.explosionfurnace.advanced=Explosion Furnace mechanics
guide.prodigytech.entry.introduction.explosionfurnace.advanced.content1=When given a redstone pulse, the Explosion Furnace will attempt to consume all Explosive and Reactant in its slots. If it succesfully did, it will produce an explosion and generate "Explosive Power" (or EP). The amount of EP generated is proportional to the amount of Explosive.
guide.prodigytech.entry.introduction.explosionfurnace.advanced.content2=At the same time, an efficiency multiplier will be calculated depending on how far from the ideal proportions the quantities of Explosive and Reactants are (for Gunpowder and Sand it's 5:4). Being further from the ideal proportions results in more items to be lost in the process.
guide.prodigytech.entry.introduction.explosionfurnace.advanced.content3=Then, inputs are run top to bottom. If there is enough EP to process one, it consumes the appropriate amount of EP and gets processed. If the recipe requires a Reagent, it will be consumed appropriately if present, and if not the input item will be lost.
guide.prodigytech.entry.introduction.explosionfurnace.advanced.content4=Explosives, Reactants, inputs and Reagents can be inserted from any side by Hoppers and such, and outputs can be extracted from any side as well. If the output slots are full while processing items, the excess items will be thrown in front of the Explosion Furnace.

#Hot Air
guide.prodigytech.entry.hotair.mechanics=Hot Air mechanics
guide.prodigytech.entry.hotair.mechanics.content1=Most machines in the mod will use Hot Air as their fuel. Hot Air can be produced with Aeroheaters, which will output their Hot Air up.\nHot Air always travels upwards and is lost when going through anything that does not let it pass.
guide.prodigytech.entry.hotair.mechanics.content2=Hot Air machines will require Hot Air to be supplied to their bottom side at a certain temperature in order to work. Some of them will also transmit their Hot Air up, with a lower temperature while working. This allows you to power several machines with the same Aeroheater.
guide.prodigytech.entry.hotair.mechanics.content3=Higher temperatures will result in machines working faster. It also indirectly allows you to chain more machines since the temperature can go through a lot more machines before being too low to be usable.
guide.prodigytech.entry.hotair.mechanics.content4=Air Funnels allows you to transfer Hot Air along longer distances without having to make expensive machines.\nIn addition, they will stop transmitting Hot Air when supplied with a redstone signal.

guide.prodigytech.entry.hotair.aeroheaters=Aeroheaters
guide.prodigytech.entry.hotair.aeroheaters.content=As said previously, Aeroheaters are what produce Hot Air. Most of them will take time to heat up and have residual heat once out of fuel. This is means it is more efficient to leave them running for a long time without stops.\nFor now you have two choices to power your machines.

guide.prodigytech.entry.hotair.aeroheaters.magmatic.content=The Magmatic Aeroheater will constantly produce low temperature Hot Air as long as it is above a Lava block (source or flowing). While it never needs refueling, it is also not hot enough to allow chaining machines or to power more advanced ones.
guide.prodigytech.entry.hotair.aeroheaters.solid.content=The Solid Fuel Aeroheater burns Furnace fuels to produce its Hot Air. This one can reach much higher temperatures, but will require a constant source of fuel to work.\nFuels can be inserted from any side except the top.

guide.prodigytech.entry.hotair.machines.grinder.content=The Rotary Grinder works like a lot of well known machines: it crushes things. Most notably, it can crush an Ore into 2 Dusts, each being smeltable into an Ingot. It has a variety of other uses, and is required to progress the mod.\nItems can be inserted/extracted from any side except top and bottom.
guide.prodigytech.entry.hotair.machines.furnace.content=The Blower Furnace is simply a Hot Air powered Furnace. While it is slower than a normal Furnace on low temperatures, it is much more fuel efficient and can be chained with other machines.\nItems can be inserted/extracted from any side except top and bottom.
guide.prodigytech.entry.hotair.machines.sawmill.content=The Heat Sawmill can cut wood much more efficiently than hands can. This includes cutting Logs into Planks, and Planks into Sticks. This process will also produce Sawdust, which can be made into Particle Board.\nItems can be inserted/extracted from any side except top and bottom.
guide.prodigytech.entry.hotair.machines.incinerator.content=The Incinerator is the simplest machine. It will take any item and turn it into Ash. This Ash has a variety of uses, including decoration and serving as a low power explosive for the Explosion Furnace.\nItems can be inserted/extracted from any side except top and bottom.

#Circuits
guide.prodigytech.entry.circuits.solderer.content1=The Solderer is a machine that can make various Circuits, which are needed for more advanced machines. It requires too much temperature for a mere Magmatic Aeroheater to fuel it.
guide.prodigytech.entry.circuits.solderer.content2=To make a Circuit, the machine needs Circuit Plates, Gold Dust and an appropriate Circuit Pattern. The latter will tell which Circuit will be made. The time spent and the amount of Gold needed depends on the Circuit made, and some of them will need an additional item to be consumed.
guide.prodigytech.entry.circuits.solderer.content3=The machine needs to melt inserted Gold Dust before being able to use it, which it will do once hot enough. All items will be automatically put in the correct slots when shift clicked or inserted through automation.\nItems can be inserted/extracted from any side except the top and bottom.

guide.prodigytech.entry.circuits.reassembler.content=The Magnetic Reassembler uses strong magnets to force small particules together. This makes it act as a reverse Rotary Grinder, and is an essential component on getting started with Energion Crystal farming.\nItems can be inserted/extracted from any side except top and bottom.

#Energion
guide.prodigytech.entry.energion.dust.content=Energion Dust is a mixture oozing with raw energy. Its main use is filling up Energion Batteries, which are required to progress further.

guide.prodigytech.entry.energion.batteries=Batteries
guide.prodigytech.entry.energion.batteries.content1=Energion Batteries are simple way of exploiting Energion. They can be manually filled with Energion Dust, ready to be used by some machines. They will eventually deplete and will need to be filled again.
guide.prodigytech.entry.energion.batteries.content2=Bigger Batteries can be made, which last longer but requires more Energion to be filled up again. All Batteries last the same amount of time per Energion Dust.

guide.prodigytech.entry.energion.aeroheater.content1=The Energion Aeroheater will be your main use of Energion Batteries. Up to 6 Energion Batteries can be inserted, all being used at the same rate. The more batteries are being used, the hotter it can get.
guide.prodigytech.entry.energion.aeroheater.content2=It can reach a maximum temperature of 80, 100, 125, 160, 200 and 250°C with 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 and 6 active Batteries, respectively. Batteries can be inserted and empty Batteries can be extracted from any side except the top.

guide.prodigytech.entry.energion.replenisher.content=The Battery Replenisher is a simple machine that will fill empty or partially depleted Energion Batteries with Energion Dust. It needs to be provided with Hot Air to work, and can only fill a single Battery at a time. Insert and extract from any side but top and bottom.

guide.prodigytech.entry.energion.crystals=Crystal Farming
guide.prodigytech.entry.energion.crystals.content1=Energion Dust can be turned into Energion Crystals in a Magnetic Reassembler. These Crystals can then be planted on the ground and will slowly grow over time, yielding more Crystals. Those can then either be replanted or grinded into useable Energion Dust.
guide.prodigytech.entry.energion.crystals.content2=Those Crystals are HIGHLY DANGEROUS once grown, and should NEVER be harvested without the Crystal Cutter. You can right click a Crystal with it to harvest only a stage at a time, or just break it to harvest it all at once.

guide.prodigytech.entry.energion.automatic.content1=The Automatic Crystal Cutter is a simple machine to automate your Energion Crystal farming. Simply power it with Hot Air and plant a crystal in front of it. When the crystal is fully grown, the Cutter will harvest it until it is back at its first stage. Extract from any side except top and bottom.
guide.prodigytech.entry.energion.automatic.content2=Since it is likely each Cutter will spend more time being inactive than active, it is possible to stack large amounts of them vertically with the minimum Hot Air requirements with minimal penalty.

#Primordium
guide.prodigytech.entry.primordium.primordialis_reactor.content1=The Primordialis Reactor is a machine that turns plant matter into Primordium. It requires heat that only an Energion Aeroheater can provide, and will need a lot of infrastructure to work at an acceptable speed. Items can be inserted/extracted from all sides except top and bottom.
guide.prodigytech.entry.primordium.primordialis_reactor.content2=Putting different items simultaneously in the Reactor will cause it to be both faster and more efficient. 9 different items at once will allow it to require roughly 9x less items and 81x less time than with a single type of item.

guide.prodigytech.entry.primordium.atomic_reshaper.content=The Atomic Reshaper can transform materials into other using varying amounts of Primordium. Most notably, it can turn Stone into random raw ores. Items can be inserted/extracted from all sides except the top and bottom.

guide.prodigytech.entry.primordium.zorra=Zorra
guide.prodigytech.entry.primordium.zorra.content1=The Zorra is an artificial breed of tree obtained by putting any Sapling through the Atomic Reshaper. Its leaves are razor sharp and can be harvested to make Zorrasteel.
guide.prodigytech.entry.primordium.zorra.content2=While Zorra Saplings are expensive and the trees don't yield a lot of them, any Zorra Leaves grown from a Sapling can absorb the blood of any creature it kills and use it to spread a few blocks.

guide.prodigytech.entry.primordium.tartaric_aeroheater.content=The Tartaric Aeroheater is the most powerful Aeroheater there is, if you can afford to run it. It burns Furnace fuel like the Solid Fuel Aeroheater, but will eat through it faster and faster as it heats up.\nFuels can be inserted from any side except the top.

guide.prodigytech.entry.primordium.zorrasteel_tools=Zorrasteel Tools
guide.prodigytech.entry.primordium.zorrasteel_tools.content=Zorrasteel can be used to make some tools. They are as strong as Diamond and are unbreakable. They also cannot receive enchantments the normal ways, for that you'll need a Zorra Altar. It also allows them to get enchanted a lot more than mundane tools.

guide.prodigytech.entry.primordium.zorra_altar.content1=The Zorra Altar is used to apply or upgrade enchantments on Zorrasteel tools, at the cost of experience and Zorra Leaves. Putting a Zorrasteel tool in it will give you 3 options to choose from as well as their cost.
guide.prodigytech.entry.primordium.zorra_altar.content2=The first slot will always be a new enchantment to apply (if possible), the second always an upgrade to an existing enchantment (if possible), and the third can be either and comes with a big experience discount, but you cannot see what it will apply.
guide.prodigytech.entry.primordium.zorra_altar.content3=With enough experience, Zorrasteel tools can receive enchantments that far surpasses what standard tools can reach, although the price will start to accumulate quickly.

guide.prodigytech.entry.primordium.mystery_treat.content1=Mystery Treats are edible candy made from reshaping Sugar. They have 1 or 2 colors, each color representing a potion effect which will be granted by eating the Treat.
guide.prodigytech.entry.primordium.mystery_treat.content2=For 2 colors Treats, a color that appears on the 2 stripes will have a weaker effect than if it appeared on the rest of the Treat. A single colored Treat will always have a stronger effect.

#Logistics
guide.prodigytech.entry.logistics.linear.content=The Linear Extractor is the simplest of the Extractors. It will quickly pull items from an inventory in front of it and push them to an inventory on the opposite side, or keep it in its small internal inventory. It can be oriented in any direction and disabled with redstone.
guide.prodigytech.entry.logistics.funnelling.content=The Funnelling Extractor is similar to the Linear one, but pulls from all 5 sides it is not pushing to. Items are pulled in a specific order, with the opposite side of the pushing one always being the first one.
guide.prodigytech.entry.logistics.wormhole.content1=The Wormhole Funnel is the only way to transmit Hot Air horizontally. It can either be placed on top or below a block, and when linked with another Wormhole Funnel in the opposite position they will transmit Hot Air between eachother.
guide.prodigytech.entry.logistics.wormhole.content2=Wormhole Funnels can be linked by using a Wormhole Linker. Right click a Funnel then the other to link them. Once linked you can right click any of the two Funnels with anything that's not a block or the Linker to show you where the other Funnel is.
guide.prodigytech.entry.logistics.wormhole.content3=A Wormhole Funnel can only be linked to another Funnel in the same dimension and less than 8 blocks away on all axis. It also can only be linked to one other Funnel at a time.